The bar was around the corner from our hotel and had a good atmosphere, my partner and i ordered food and then tried to order a couple of drinks. The bar staff said that he would find out if the kitchen was still open as it was about 8pm. He then walked to the other side of the bar and spoke to 2 female customers for 5 minutes and then came bacl to us and asked us if we wanted to order anything before he then had to go and check if the kitchen was open again. He was incapable of making a cocktail other than the premade ones off the menu because he said it was to busy even though the bar was clear. When the food came it was very nice and the only saving grace. We ended up drinking pepsi. Also when i attempted to pay the bill he disappeared again after putting it through and left me stood there while he ran off to speak to another female customer who was leaving. Shame because it has alot of potential
